      h3 2015: Time for a Climate Coalition?
      p
        |When: 6:30pm 19th February 2015
        |Where: Physics Lecture 3, Blackett Building, South Kensington Campus, Imperial College
        |How Much: Free!
        |We are proud to welcome Tom Burke (pictured left) to speak on the future directions of climate change policy and sustainability.
        |Tom has exceptional experience in the field. He is the Chairman of <a href='http://www.e3g.org/'> E3G, Third Generation Environmentalism</a>, and an Environmental Policy Adviser to <a href='http://www.riotinto.com/'> Rio Tinto plc </a>. He is also a Visiting Professor at both Imperial and UCL. He is a member of the External Review Committee of Shell and the Sustainable Sourcing Advisory Board of Unilever. He has advised the government over many years on issues of environmental and sustainability policy.
        |The talk will be followed by a time for questions from the audience and will draw to a formal close at 7:30 at which point light refreshments will be provided.
      br
