      h3 LFSP Freshers' Workshop: Scientists, politics and how thinking in tanks can help
      p
        |When: 6:00pm 16th October 2014
        |Where: Room 1004, Blackett Building, South Kensington Campus, Imperial College
        |How Much: Free!
        |With Dr. Jason Blackstock, Senior Lecturer in Science and Global Affairs
        |An active and engaging workshop focusing on the role of science in public policy, how scientists can get involved and where LFSP fits in.
        |Dr. Blackstock has worked across the globe at the junction between science and public policy and now leads the UCL Department for Science, Technology, Engineering and Public Policy.
        |The workshop will begin promptly at 6:00pm so come a bit beforehand. It will run until 7:30 after which drinks and light refreshments will be provided.
